Overview
This repository contains the security assessment report and vulnerable machine used in an academic Capture The Flag (CTF) exercise.

The assessment simulates a real-world internal penetration test conducted against a deliberately vulnerable system named **cyber-server**, with the objective of achieving full system compromise (root access).

---

Assessment Scope
- Internal penetration testing
- Web application exploitation
- Credential attacks
- Privilege escalation
- Post-exploitation analysis

**Target IP:** `192.168.56.104`  
**Testing Methodology:** Inspired by NIST SP 800-115

---

Tools Used
- Netdiscover
- Nmap
- Hydra
- SSH
- Linux privilege escalation techniques

---

 Flags Summary
| Flag | Description | Location |
|-----|------------|----------|
| Flag 1 | Web Application Exploitation | Port 8080 |
| Flag 2 | User Access | `/home/engineer_alpha/user.txt` |
| Flag 3 | Root Access | `/root/root.txt` |
